docs.abstract: Digital fingerprints link pro-Russian and anti-European websites, part of an online ecosystem that is sowing discord ahead of European elections this month.
docs.snippet: Digital fingerprints link pro-Russian and anti-European websites, part of an online ecosystem that is sowing discord ahead of European elections this month.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Less than two weeks before pivotal elections for the European Parliament, a constellation of websites and social media accounts linked to Russia or far-right groups is spreading disinformation, encouraging discord and amplifying distrust in the centrist parties that have governed for decades.

headline.main: Russia Is Targeting Europe’s Elections. So Are Far-Right Copycats.
headline.print_headline: Hackers Sow Discord as Vote Looms in Europe

docs.abstract: Ava DuVernay’s mini-series depicts the excruciating toll that persecution and incarceration had on the teenage boys known as the Central Park Five.
docs.snippet: Ava DuVernay’s mini-series depicts the excruciating toll that persecution and incarceration had on the teenage boys known as the Central Park Five.
docs.lead_paragraph: I was 13, a mere year younger than Kevin Richardson and Raymond Santana, two of the boys who made up Central Park Five, when they were wrongfully convicted of beating and raping the white female jogger Trisha Meili in 1989.

headline.main: ‘When They See Us’ Transforms Its Victims Into Heroes
headline.print_headline: Showing the Accused Were Victims, Too

docs.abstract: As students demand the renaming of buildings whose names pay tribute to polarizing historical figures, universities are at a loss for easy solutions.
docs.snippet: As students demand the renaming of buildings whose names pay tribute to polarizing historical figures, universities are at a loss for easy solutions.
docs.lead_paragraph: College campuses have long been centers of social foment and student activism. In the 1960s, they were magnets for protests over the Vietnam War, and more recently, the Black Lives Matter movement forced schools to confront issues of racial justice and inclusion.

headline.main: When the Names on Campus Buildings Evoke a Racist Past
headline.print_headline: On Campus, Finding Ways To Honor a Place’s History While Denouncing Racism

docs.abstract: A recent episode of the CBS drama “The Red Line” featured a gay romance involving a Muslim character. Fawzia Mirza, the episode’s writer, discusses how it came to be.
docs.snippet: A recent episode of the CBS drama “The Red Line” featured a gay romance involving a Muslim character. Fawzia Mirza, the episode’s writer, discusses how it came to be.
docs.lead_paragraph: If Fawzia Mirza didn’t start seeing people like herself on screen, she felt like she “was going to die.”

headline.main: Queer Muslims Are Still Rare on TV. One Writer Wants to Change That.
headline.print_headline: Seeking Ways to Put Queer Muslims Onscreen

docs.abstract: Disciplinary proceedings against Officer Daniel Pantaleo, who is accused of using a chokehold to subdue Mr. Garner, could lead to his firing.
docs.snippet: Disciplinary proceedings against Officer Daniel Pantaleo, who is accused of using a chokehold to subdue Mr. Garner, could lead to his firing.
docs.lead_paragraph: The last words Eric Garner, an unarmed black man, uttered on a New York City sidewalk in 2014 instantly became a national rallying cry against police brutality. “I can’t breathe,’’ Mr. Garner pleaded 11 times after a police officer in plain clothes placed his arm across his neck and pulled him to the ground while other officers handcuffed him.

headline.main: ‘I Can’t Breathe’: 5 Years After Eric Garner’s Death, an Officer Faces Trial
headline.print_headline: Police Officer Who Heard ‘I Can’t Breathe’ Goes to Trial
